Detailed Description

3GPP TS 23.040 V5.1.0 - Attention: This class is a wrapper over a TPDU-reference (no data is copied). Only the anchor of the byte-stream is needed the initialize the access to the class members.

enum Sms::WarningLevel
 

describes the warning level for the sms memory.

Enumerator:
CapacityExceed  memory capacity is exceeded - sms couldn't be stored.
SimIsFull  on the SIM there are no free position, but operation is requested on the SIM only (saving of the SMS class 2).
SimNotUsed  SMS class2 is received, but MN view is set to only nvram storage.
NoSmsOnSim  SMS class2 is received, but on the SIM there are no SMS.
WarningSimIsFull  The last free SMS entry on the SIM card is used.
SimStorageGetsFree  SMS storage on the SIM card gets free again .
MemoryFull  memory is full - last sms, which could be stored, backwards compatible
